page.title: 19 Local News
page.content:
News itams from East Fife Mail 5/7/85.
More tourists from America,Canada and Europe visit Leven this holiday period probably because of the good exchange rates for the dollar.
Epidemic year for measles and whooping cough.Doctors have appealed to parents not to put off having their children immunised.
Jobs for Levenmouth? An application has been lodged for planning permission to build industrial units,a supermarket,a sports complex,shops,car park and housing at a derelict site at Methil docks.It will cost Â£4.5 million and provide two hundred jobs.
